Here are both approaches:

**1. Register the route** in `AppShell.xaml.cs`:

```csharp
public AppShell()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
}
```

**2. Navigate from ProductListPage** — two options:

```csharp
// Approach A: String query parameter (product ID only)
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");

// Approach B: Full object via ShellNavigationQueryParameters
var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
{
    { "product", product }
};
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
```

**3. Receive on the ViewModel** with `IQueryAttributable`:

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId
    {
        get => _productId;
        set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value);
    }

    public Product Product
    {
        get => _product;
        set => SetProperty(ref _product, value);
    }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A: string parameter arrives as a string
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service, DB, etc.
        }

        // Approach B: full object arrives as-is (no serialization)
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
            ProductId = p.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

**4. Wire the ViewModel** on `ProductDetailsPage`:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.ProductDetailsPage"
             x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailsViewModel">
    <!-- page content bound to ProductDetailsViewModel properties -->
</ContentPage>
```

**Key differences:**

| | Query string (`?productId=...`) | `ShellNavigationQueryParameters` |
|---|---|---|
| **Data type** | String only | Any object |
| **Serialization** | URL-encoded string | None (passed by reference) |
| **Use when** | You have a simple ID and will load data on the target page | You already have the object in memory |

> **Tip:** Always `await` `GoToAsync` — fire-and-forget causes race conditions. And use `ContentTemplate` with `DataTemplate` in your Shell hierarchy so pages load on demand rather than at startup.
